.TH "zynqmp_disp_layer_update" 9 "zynqmp_disp_layer_update" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
zynqmp_disp_layer_update \- Update the layer framebuffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" zynqmp_disp_layer_update
.BI "(struct zynqmp_disp_layer *layer "  ","
.BI "struct drm_plane_state *state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "layer" 12
The layer
.IP "state" 12
The plane state
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Update the framebuffer for the layer by issuing a new DMA engine transaction
for the new framebuffer.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, or the DMA descriptor failure error otherwise
